it, ISIS
fighters.

00:50.384 --> 00:58.025 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All that and
more on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:58.058 --> 01:00.928 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:00.961 --> 01:10.537 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: From the top
of Trump Tower
in New York on down, the message
today was

01:10.570 --> 01:14.441 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
emphatic: There is no turmoil in
the transition.

01:14.474 --> 01:19.846 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
News accounts told of more
moderate figures
being purged, of advisers
fighting for power,

01:19.880 --> 01:22.950 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and of foreign officials unable
to reach Trump
aides.

01:22.983 --> 01:26.253 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The president-elect denied it
all in a series
of tweets.

01:26.286 --> 01:30.390 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Instead, he wrote, it is going
so smoothly,
and his spokesman echoed the
claim.

01:30.424 --> 01:34.962 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JASON MILLER, Trump Campaign
Senior Communications
Adviser: Inside, there's a very
solid plan.

01:34.995 --> 01:38.865 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's a methodical approach to
all this
being put together.

01:38.899 --> 01:44.705 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have read a number of the news
reports that
want to make us kind of like --
there's all

01:44.738 --> 01:45.706 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
sorts of descriptions I have
heard.

01:45.739 --> 01:47.441 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's very calm, it's very
structured.

01:47.474 --> 01:49.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And anyone saying anything else
is either,
A, bitter because they're not on
the inside

01:49.509 --> 01:53.347 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and not being considered, or
they're someone
who is just bitter because the
election was

01:53.380 --> 01:56.950 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
last week and they didn't get
the result that
they wanted.

01:56.984 --> 02:00.687 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Meanwhile, in
Washington,
vice president-elect Pence met
with Vice President

02:00.721 --> 02:05.993 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Biden, who said he's confident
everything
will be in good hands on day one
of the new

02:06.026 --> 02:07.661 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
administration.

02:07.694 --> 02:11.665 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But House Democrats formally
asked that Steve
Bannon not be made a senior
adviser.

02:11.698 --> 02:16.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They cited allegations of racial
bigotry and
anti-Semitism, which Bannon
denies.

02:16.370 --> 02:21.341 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Obama also offered
reassurance about
the political transition on his
farewell tour

02:21.375 --> 02:23.110 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of Europe.

02:23.143 --> 02:26.947 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mr. Obama visited the ancient
Acropolis in
Athens, Greece, the cradle of
democracy.

02:26.980 --> 02:30.484 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And in a speech, he again
promised a peaceful
handover of power.

02:30.517 --> 02:33.954 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
As you may have noticed, the
next American

02:33.987 --> 02:36.656 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
president and I could not be
more different.

02:36.690 --> 02:37.657 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

02:37.691 --> 02:39.393 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(APPLAUSE)

02:39.426 --> 02:43.997 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: We have very
different points
of view, but American democracy
is bigger

02:44.031 --> 02:45.399 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
than any one person.

02:45.432 --> 02:48.468 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: From Greece,
the president
flew on to Germany.

02:48.502 --> 02:53.907 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president of Turkey today
criticized anti-Trump
protesters in the U.S. Recep
Tayyip Erdogan

02:53.940 --> 02:59.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
said his message is show some
respect and
wait to see how he actually
governs.

02:59.713 --> 03:05.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And in a TV interview, Syrian
President Bashar
al-Assad praised Mr. Trump's
campaign comments

03:05.419 --> 03:07.921 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on fighting Islamic State forces
in Syria.

03:07.954 --> 03:11.558 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BASHAR AL-ASSAD, President of
Syria (through
translator): If -- I say if --
if he is going

03:11.591 --> 03:16.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to fight the terrorists, of
course, we're
going to be ally, natural ally
in that regard,

03:16.830 --> 03:18.832 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
with the Russians, with
Iranians, with many
other countries.

03:18.865 --> 03:22.469 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The
president-elect has
said he would prioritize
fighting ISIS over

03:22.502 --> 03:24.938 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
regime change in Syria.

03:24.971 --> 03:28.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Russia, the Supreme Court has
overturned
a criminal conviction against
opposition leader

03:28.975 --> 03:30.777 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Alexei Navalny.

03:30.811 --> 03:34.514 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He was convicted for
embezzlement in 2013,
but, in February, the European
Court of Human

03:34.548 --> 03:38.051 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Rights ruled his right to a fair
trial had
been violated.

03:38.085 --> 03:43.223 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Navalny will now get a new
trial, but that
could still hinder him from
running for office

03:43.256 --> 03:45.125 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
again.

03:45.158 --> 03:48.562 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Back in this country, a
Minnesota policeman
was charged today with
second-degree manslaughter

03:48.595 --> 03:52.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the killing of Philando
Castile during
a traffic stop last summer.

03:52.966 --> 03:58.538 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Officer Jeronimo Yanez has said
he opened
fire after Castile said he was
armed and appeared

03:58.572 --> 04:00.173 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to be reaching for something.

04:00.207 --> 04:04.911 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The aftermath was streamed live
by his girlfriend
and triggered protests.

04:04.945 --> 04:08.548 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A prosecutor said today the
shooting was totally
unjustified.

04:08.582 --> 04:14.287 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOHN CHOI, Ramsey County
Prosecutor: To those
who may say that this incident
was Philando

04:14.321 --> 04:24.264 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Castile's fault, I would submit
that no reasonable
officer, knowing, seeing and
hearing what

04:24.297 --> 04:31.471 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Officer Yanez did at the time,
would've used
deadly force under these
circumstances.

04:31.505 --> 04:36.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Yanez could be
sentenced
to up to 10 years in prison if
he's convicted.

04:36.776 --> 04:39.212 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Republicans and Democrats in the
Senate picked
their leaders today.

04:39.246 --> 04:43.350 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Kentucky Republican Mitch
McConnell was reelected
to serve as majority leader.

04:43.383 --> 04:47.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
New York Democrat Chuck Schumer
will take
over as minority leader,
replacing the retiring

04:47.287 --> 04:48.788 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Harry Reid.

04:48.822 --> 04:51.958 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Both men talked of looking past
the election
and cooperating where they can.

04:51.992 --> 04:53.760 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

04:53.793 --> 04:55.495 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MITCH MCCONNELL (R-KY), Majority
Leader: we're
going to address the real
concerns of the

04:55.529 --> 05:01.668 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
American people, not go back and
relitigate
what anybody on either side may
have said

05:01.701 --> 05:04.237 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
during a very hotly contested
presidential
race.

05:04.271 --> 05:05.639 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

05:05.672 --> 05:07.974 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLES SCHUMER (D), New York:
Where we can
work together, we will.

05:08.008 --> 05:12.279 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I have also said to the
president-elect,
on issues where we disagree, you
can expect

05:12.312 --> 05:14.214 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a strong and tough fight.

05:14.247 --> 05:17.784 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The Democrats'
new leadership
team also includes former
presidential candidate

05:17.817 --> 05:19.553 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Bernie Sanders.

