national security
jobs, foreign policy positions.

07:14.968 --> 07:16.703 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What's the latest?

07:16.736 --> 07:19.939 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Well, the
latest is, Hari,
that to experienced foreign
policy hands,

07:19.973 --> 07:22.509 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the process looks chaotic.

07:22.542 --> 07:26.179 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have names being raised --
for instance,
let's take secretary of state.

07:26.212 --> 07:30.817 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You have John Bolton, the former
U.N. ambassador,
very kind of aggressive, you
would call a

07:30.850 --> 07:32.819 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
neoconservative.

07:32.852 --> 07:37.757 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then you have Senator Bob
Corker, who is considered
sort of middle of the road and
conservative.

07:37.791 --> 07:42.362 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then you have Rudy Giuliani,
of course,
the former New York mayor.

07:42.395 --> 07:47.901 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A few other names have surfaced,
Kelly Ayotte,
Nikki Haley, the South Carolina
governor.

07:47.934 --> 07:54.140 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But what troubles those who are
really observing
this process is there seems to
be no rhyme

07:54.174 --> 07:55.508 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
