09:08.181 --> 09:12.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: One ambassador
said to me,
very reassuring words, but we
want to hear

09:12.519 --> 09:15.188 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
them from president-elect Trump.

09:15.221 --> 09:18.425 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As you said, President Obama
will be meeting
with Chancellor Merkel tomorrow.

09:18.458 --> 09:23.496 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They have private meetings
before he goes
in meetings with other NATO
allies.

09:23.530 --> 09:29.235 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What concerns the Europeans
deeply are two
things that Donald Trump said
during the campaign.

09:29.269 --> 09:32.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One was, he questioned the whole
relevance
of the NATO alliance and in fact
some of our

09:32.605 --> 09:36.776 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
alliances overseas, the burden
that the United
States pays to support them.

09:36.810 --> 09:42.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he actually suggested that
maybe NATO
wouldn't come to the rescue some
of country

09:42.182 --> 09:47.120 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
if it hadn't been -- under
Article V if it
hadn't been paying its full fair
share, which

09:47.153 --> 09:49.622 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is supposed to be 2 percent of
GDP.

09:49.656 --> 09:55.829 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so Wolfgang Ischinger, who
used to be
the German ambassador here --
and I spoke

09:55.862 --> 10:00.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to Ambassador Ischinger late
last night -- and
he said, these are really
dangerous times

10:00.433 --> 10:01.401 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for Europe.

